results.name: Minimal set of prime-strings in base 10.
comment: Any prime number contains in its digits at least one of the term of this sequence and there is no smaller set. There are 26 terms in the sequence.
link: Ioulia N. Baoulina, Martin Kreh, Jörn Steuding, Deleting digits, arXiv:1607.01548 [math.NT], 2016.

J. Shallit, Minimal primes, pdf, J. Recreational Mathematics, vol. 30.2, pp. 113-117, 1999-2000.
